                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17171016-10-off59 t17171016-10-cd60"></join> last. Several Evidences deposed, that hearing a Cry of stop Thief, they pursued the Prisoner into George-yard in Lombard-street, and apprehended him, and that just before his Apprehension, they saw the Callico drop from him. The Prisoner pretended a Man gave it him to carry to the Bell Alehouse in Grace-Church-street. But that Pretence would scarce have availed him, but that he had the good Luck to have been dealing with a Quaker who would not swear, and so that lucky Scrupulosity, in all probability, saved him; for the Jury were obliged to <rs id="t17171016-10-verdict61" type="verdictDescription">
